Police confirmed that a security guard had been shot and killed at Woestalleen Mine on Monday, March 29. The deceased has been identified as Mokgabudi Andries Kgawane. Police say Mr Kgawane and his colleagues were confronted by “an unauthorized group of unknown individuals,” shortly before 21:00. The trespassers attacked the security guards with rocks, while shots were also fired at them. Mr Kgawane died after a bullet struck him during the attack. There’s been no arrests.